            "answer_text": "Hey, Hannah. Thank you for your question. Come, let\u2019s have a look at it. Is the word \"a lot\" one word or two words? A lot is two words e.g. I do not have a lot of money, that\u2019s it! When it comes to the one word of a lot it becomes \u2018allot\u2019 e.g. \"equal time was allotted to each\" i.e. give or apportion (something) to someone. synonyms: Allocate, assign, issue, award, grant, administer or devote. I trust that will help to distinguish between the two. Good luck. Kind regards, Bye. ",
